==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Maw
<hw>Maw</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>mawe</ets>, AS.
<ets>maga</ets> stomach; akin to D. <ets>maag</ets>, OHG.
<ets>mago</ets>, G. <ets>magen</ets>, Icel. <ets>magi</ets>, Sw.
<ets>mage</ets>, Dan. <ets>mave</ets>. ⟦root⟧103.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A stomach; the receptacle into which food is taken by swallowing;
in birds, the craw; -- now used only of the lower animals, except
humorously or in contempt.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Bellies and <qex>maws</qex> of living creatures.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Appetite; inclination.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unless you had more <qex>maw</qex> to do me good.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fish maw</b></col>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Fish</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maw</ent>⟦br⟧

